Lunch in the courtyard is a taster of the delights available each evening in the dining room of the big house. You can combine a visit with a short cookery course and tour of the shell house garden. Next day have lunch in the Farmgate Caf√© (farmgate.ie) in Cork city and then travel west to Durrus and the Blairscove restaurant (blairscove.ie), where the buffet of starters entices you into ever more pleasing tastes from their menu plus wine selection, along with a further buffet for puddings. The setting on the bay is magical and the inspired design of the accommodation transports you to another world. Alternatively, head to northern Spain, to enjoy the delights of a rioja vineyard at the Marques de Riscal Hotel in Elciego (hotel-marquesderiscal.com). It was designed by Frank Gehry and after you have acclimatised to the wonderful architecture, take a tour of the vineyard. The gastronomic restaurant offers the best of local flavours all accompanied by their wines, guided by the most helpful staff in the world.
